# Secrets are local-only. This file carries variable NAMES only — never real
# values. Copy it to `.env.nosync` (git-ignored) and fill in the values there;
# load them with `source ./load-env.sh`. `.env.nosync` is never committed and is
# excluded from every backup tier (see BACKUP-RECOVERY.md, Tier 3).
#
# Add one line per secret a connector needs, of the form NAME= (no value here).
# Connector manifests reference these by name under auth.vars (see
# Connectors/connector-template.manifest.yaml). Example shape (commented out):
#
#   ORACLE_EXAMPLE_API_TOKEN=
#   ORACLE_EXAMPLE_DB_URL=
#
# Leave this file with NAMES ONLY. The secret scanner (secret_scan) runs over the
# tree and will flag any real-looking value committed here.
